OL,6,FFollowing the verdict, the family of
OL,7,FMichael Riddiough-Allen issued a
OL,8,Fstatement.
OL,10,FIt reads: "The journey that has led us
OL,11,Fhere from the night Michael died,
OL,12,Fthough long and painful, has opened
OL,13,Four eyes to the growing problem in our
OL,14,Fsociety. This journey has given us the
OL,15,Fpurpose and motivation to try to make
OL,16,Fa difference.
OL,18,F"Whilst we are grateful for our
OL,19,Fjustice system and its ability to
OL,20,Fuphold the laws of our society,
OL,21,Ftoday's verdicts are not a victory.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
