OL,3,CKnifeman guilty of murdering rugby
OL,4,Cplayer in rampage outside nightclub
OL,6,F"Michael watched that violence unfold
OL,7,Fin front of him, he felt a need to
OL,8,Fintervene to remove the threat and
OL,9,Fprotect others. In this task, he lost
OL,10,Fhis life.
OL,12,F"As four families we stand before you,
OL,13,Ftogether, to raise awareness of the
OL,14,Fdamage that can be caused by carrying
OL,15,Fa knife. No good can come of it, only
OL,16,Fanger, hatred, loss and grief.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/9
