OL,4,Cplayer in rampage outside nightclub
OL,6,F"We aim to educate and to work
OL,7,Fcollaboratively to tackle the root of
OL,8,Fthe problem. To help our young people
OL,9,Funderstand that a knife does not
OL,10,Fprotect you or make you popular. To
OL,11,Fgive them the skills and tools needed
OL,12,Fto make better choices in the future.
OL,14,F"We stand here together, as a warning;
OL,15,Fif a change does not happen then many
OL,16,Fmore families will stand on court
OL,17,Fsteps, broken from the loss that knife
OL,18,Fcrime brings."
